msg-mo4sldk7-afebeec1d	conv_1776543974467_wjzcahz	assistant	\n\nOkay, let me get the lay of the land first — checking what you already have going and what task types are available.Okay cool, clean slate. Let me think about how to organize this.\n\nSo you've basically got a move-out with the end goal of getting to Glacier. I'm hearing a bunch of distinct areas/tasks, and I think the best way to structure this is:\n\n1. **An endeavor** — "Move Out" as the big-picture goal\n2. **Individual tasks** grouped by area — so you can walk through room by room and check things off\n\nBefore I start creating stuff, the existing task types are Focus and Errand. I think we'd benefit from a couple more — like a **Physical/Packing** type for the hands-on apartment work and maybe keep **Errand** for the runs (storage unit, buying bubble wrap, getting guitar cases). Sound good?\n\nHere's how I'd break down what you listed:\n\n**Bedroom:**\n- Take down HEMNES cabinet\n- Gather personal items from bedroom\n\n**Kitchen/Living:**\n- Pack coffee stuff from kitchen table\n- Go through coffee table items + decorations\n\n**Closet:**\n- Dispose of broken guitar\n- Go through clothes on floor\n- Go through shoes\n- Move sleeping bags to car\n- Clothes rack → keep pile (transport)\n\n**Bathroom:**\n- Go through toiletry drawers\n\n**Office/Tech:**\n- Pack personal PC\n- Unmount monitor arm from wall\n\n**Art/Fragile:**\n- Buy bubble wrap for art pieces\n- Wrap and pack art pieces\n\n**Errands/Logistics:**\n- Get guitar cases from storage\n- Pack up guitars (after cases retrieved)\n- Grab cooler\n\nWant me to create all of these as individual tasks under a "Move Out" endeavor? I can make the packing type first and then bang them all out. Or if you'd rather organize it differently — like one big workflow checklist instead of separate tasks — lemme know.	[{"toolCallId":"toolu_014HTj4Fd6FgpF1D1B81XzEv","toolName":"get_tasks","toolInput":{},"category":"read","result":[]},{"toolCallId":"toolu_019eePS