msg-mo4smdhm-3aa1207fc	conv_1776543974467_wjzcahz	assistant	\n\nGot it. So two workflows:\n\n**Workflow 1 — In-apartment packing/tasks (Focus type):**\n1. Take down HEMNES cabinet\n2. Gather personal items from bedroom\n3. Pack coffee stuff from kitchen table\n4. Go through coffee table items + decorations\n5. Dispose of broken guitar\n6. Go through clothes on floor\n7. Go through shoes\n8. Move sleeping bags to car\n9. Clothes rack → transport to car\n10. Go through toiletry drawers\n11. Pack personal PC\n12. Unmount monitor arm from wall\n13. Wrap and pack art pieces (after bubble wrap is bought)\n14. Pack up guitars (after cases retrieved)\n15. Grab cooler\n\n**Workflow 2 — Errands (Errand type):**\n1. Buy bubble wrap for art pieces\n2. Get guitar cases from storage\n\nThe art wrapping and guitar packing in workflow 1 depend on the errands being done first, but since they're in separate workflows I can't set cross-workflow dependencies — we'll just have to keep that in mind.\n\nHow long do you think each of these steps takes roughly? Or want me to just throw like 10-15 min estimates on most of them and you can adjust? Also — importance/urgency, I'm thinking both pretty high since you want to get to Glacier today or tomorrow?	[]	2026-04-18 20:32:04.042
