msg-mosyhh4j-82193b41a	conv_1777993959236_jwej44q	assistant	\n\nLet me pull everything together.Okay, here's the full estimate vs. actual breakdown for completed steps:\n\n## Estimate Accuracy Report\n\n| Step | Estimated | Actual Logged | Ratio | Notes |\n|------|-----------|---------------|-------|-------|\n| **Make proto changes** | 15m (original) → 42m (revised) | 42m + 52m (duplicate session) | ~42m real | **2.8x original estimate.** We revised it after the fact to 42m. |\n| **Wait for proto build** | 15m async | ~15-20m | ✅ About right | |\n| **Get old DuckDB tool running** | 10m | 10m | ✅ **Spot on** | |\n| **Amend config for new entity type flag** | 10m | ~1m logged | Way under? | Session was only 1 min — did this actually take longer? |\n| **Verify proto CL runs without errors** | 5m | 12-18m (still in progress) | **3.6x+** | Blocked by slow laptop build/setup. Unusual circumstance. |\n| **Patch MCP server** | n/a (unplanned) | ~14m | — | Opportunistic work during wait |\n| **Update Claude Code memory files** | n/a (unplanned) | ~14m | — | Opportunistic work during wait |\n| **Find rc log cases** | n/a (unplanned) | ~14m | — | Opportunistic work during wait |\n\n## Key Takeaways\n\n1. **The "Verify proto CL" blowup is a first-time setup cost**, not a recurring pattern. You flagged this yourself — laptop repo setup, slow internet. Future runs should be closer to 5m. I wouldn't adjust the estimate for ongoing steps.\n\n2. **The original "Make proto changes" at 15m → actual 42m is the real signal.** That's code change work that hit unexpected complexity (two branches instead of one). We already restructured the workflow for this, so the remaining code steps should be better estimated.\n\n3. **"Amend config" shows 1m logged** — was that actually quick or did it get lumped into another session?\n\n4. **You're really good at productively filling async wait time.** You knocked out 3 unplanned tasks during build waits. That's a pattern worth keeping — the scheduler should account for it by having small tasks ready during async waits.\n\n5. **For remaining estimates**, the ones I'd watch are:\n   - **Make python eval code changes (20m)** — given proto changes took 42m, this might also run long. Want to bump it to 30-35m?\n   - **Push proto CL / Push eval CL (10m / 5m)** — these seem reasonable if the build is already done\n   - **Import suites into DuckDB tool (20m)** — new task, hard to calibrate\n\nWhat do you think — want to adjust any of the remaining estimates?Also saved a couple observations to memory — the laptop setup situation and your async-wait multitasking pattern. Those'll help me plan better in future sessions.	[{"toolCallId":"toolu_01M6tQnLH9rsfpppgpUh4ARC","toolName":"get_task_detail","toolInput":{"id":"task-mosses5x"},"category":"read","result":null},{"toolCallId":"toolu_012qKwD6z7qNmbMKKgLR8mx4","toolName":"get_work_sessions","toolInput":{"date":"2026-05-05"},"category":"read","result":[{"id":"wsession-mosvcvaj-1e5f20894","taskId":"task-mosses61-c0319d383","stepId":"step-mosses5x-93a43e09a","patternId":null,"blockId":null,"type":null,"startTime":"2026-05-05T15:55:00.000Z","endTime":"2026-05-05T16:05:00.000Z","plannedMinutes":0,"actualMinutes":10,"notes":"Got caught up on DuckDB branch, ran it, got it working","pomodoroCycleId":null,"createdAt":"2026-05-05T16:55:07.634Z","Task":{"id":"task-mosses61-c0319d383","name":"Wait Condition Fusion Evaluator Work","duration":256,"importance":7,"urgency":7,"type":"type-mossejmk-2859710ab","category":"work","asyncWaitTime":0,"dependencies":"[]","completed":false,"completedAt":null,"actualDuration":null,"notes":"Conditional logic notes:\\\\n- Steps 3a/3b/4 are the \\\\\\"configs are stale\\\\\\" path. If configs are current in step 2, skip these and go straight to step 5.\\\\n- Step 5 depends on step 2 so work can begin immediately if configs are fine. If configs were stale, manually re-wire step 5 to depend on step 4 (the async wait) once the new suite runs complete.\\\\n