msg-mp2sa0tp-61d9d6ebc	conv_1778599507876_sev70ao	assistant	Okay, this is a lot — but good stuff. You've clearly been thinking about all of this, and I like the approach of going layer by layer. Let me start by seeing what task types and endeavors already exist, and what memories I have from before, so we're not rebuilding from scratch.Okay, truly a blank slate — no existing types, endeavors, tasks, or memories. Fresh start. That's actually clean, we can build it right.\n\nLet me save some foundational stuff I just learned about you before we forget:Alright, context saved. Now let's do **Step 1: Task Types.**\n\nGoing through everything you listed, here's what I'm thinking for categories. These are the "buckets" that let you match tasks to schedule blocks:\n\n| Type | Emoji | What it covers |\n|------|-------|----------------|\n| **Quick Comms** | 💬 | Texts, short messages, quick replies (Alec, mom, Sergio, Kevin, Richard, etc.) |\n| **Errands** | 🚗 | Out-of-the-house stuff — firewood, trash run, Home Depot, shopping |\n| **Housework** | 🧹 | Laundry, dishes, sink cleaning, tidying, fridge cleanout, unpacking |\n| **Admin / Finances** | 💰 | Hyundai payment, monthly finances, Rocket Money, cancel subscriptions, cancel utilities, truck tags |\n| **Research / Planning** | 🔍 | Junk removal research, beep collar research, studio monitors, trip planning, time off planning, concert lookup |\n| **Creative / Music** | 🎸 | Songwriting practice, learn a song, set list, go through recordings for Charlie |\n| **Tech Setup** | 🖥️ | Vision Pro server, personal blog |\n| **Social / Relationships** | 🤝 | Plan visits (Shay, mom, Kevin, Alex, Brett), Ian hangout, send baby gift, Oregon trip scheduling |\n| **Dog Care** | 🐕 | Beep collar purchase, high value rewards, dog sitter/trainer research |\n\nA few questions before I create these:\n\n1. **Quick Comms vs. just folding texts into whatever endeavor they belong to** — do you like having a dedicated type so you can batch all your texts/messages into one block? Or would you rather tag them by context (e.g., a text to Richard about the hot tub is "Housework")?\n\n2. **Research/Planning feels broad** — it covers trip planning, product research, and life admin research. Want to split that, or keep it as one bucket since the *energy* of those tasks feels similar (sitting down, looking stuff up, making decisions)?\n\n3. **Dog Care as its own type vs. folding into Errands** — the buying stuff is errand-y, but the trainer research is more planning. Separate type, or split those items across Errands and Research?\n\n4. Anything I'm missing or miscategorizing?	[{"toolCallId":"toolu_01XthJGbrbXvb3oHvsNHDbqp","toolName":"get_task_types","toolInput":{},"category":"read","result":[]},{"toolCallId":"toolu_01AuQTVrDzDPTkjGiyR6AevU","toolName":"get_endeavors","toolInput":{"includeArchived":true},"category":"read","result":[]},{"toolCallId":"toolu_01Rg6ZbsLQ5acD4eMStEEsAi","toolName":"get_memories","toolInput":{},"category":"read","result":[]},{"toolCallId":"toolu_01ESzo4ST65YwHrChC4Q4LMb","toolName":"get_tasks","toolInput":{"includeArchived":true},"category":"read","result":[]},{"toolCallId":"toolu_01EJFv1DbVa4bu2st9dVHag3","toolName":"save_memory","toolInput":{"category":"fact","key":"living_situation","value":"Lives in a dome near Glacier/Bellingham, WA.","confidence":1},"category":"read","result":{"id":"mem-mp2s9n9c-e819f6a8a","sessionId":"session_1778599501542_iwfaxha","category":"fact","key":"living_situation","value":"Lives in a dome near Glacier/Bellingham, WA.","confidence":1,"source":"agent_observed","pinned":false,"createdAt":"2026-05-12T15:26:20.160Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-12T15:26:20.160Z","lastAccessedAt":"2026-05-12T15:26:20.160Z"}},{"toolCallId":"toolu_01VLtdBPfSgyhngr8xWKLWhT","toolName":"save_memory","toolInput":{"category":"fact","key":"dog","value":"Has a dog named Woody who needs training and off-leash work.","confidence":1},"category":"read","result":{"id":"mem-mp2s9n9f-3e85376a7","sessionId"