summary-mo92ouj8-e0ceedc82	session_1776709103518_hc4cf62	conv_1776802016388_44oou48	The user checked in after a productive morning that started at 6 AM with stretching, a 45-minute hike with their dog Woody, then ~4h45m of work on 3 high-priority NVIDIA tasks (none completed but progress shown). During a break they ordered custom engraved dog tags. The assistant logged all activities and scheduled the rest of the day with extended work time since the user took ADHD meds, plus health, music, and cleanliness blocks.	["Split remaining NVIDIA work into: trainings, query updates (waiting on run), 30 min toy viz extension for Adnan, and query compiler work for wait condition entities","Scheduled 4-hour NVIDIA work block (1:30-5:30 PM) to capitalize on ADHD meds day with buffer to get ahead","Evening schedule: 1hr health break (5:30-6:30), music block (6:30-8:00), 1hr cleanliness block (8:00-9:00)","Entity type migration task for Jia set to waiting status since enough progress was shown"]	[]	10	2026-04-21 20:25:00.308
summary-mo93uqqg-220563b7f	session_1776026596470_zisip0d	conv_1776804277077_pe7byte	\n\n```json\n{\n  "summary": "The user and assistant managed task priorities and sprint planning. They created a task for responding to Jia's Slack code review on the entity types data update CL, reprioritized all tasks (deprioritizing mandatory trainings since manager is away, elevating suite investigation, road graph KPI dashboard, and Jia response), and began re-estimating the Wait Condition Fusion workflow steps.",\n  "keyDecisions": [\n    "Created high-urgency task for responding to Jia's code review on entity types CL (data update, not analyzer update)",\n    "Deprioritized mandatory trainings since manager is out of the country, but kept them high enough to fill waiting gaps",\n    "Top priorities set: Respond to Jia (U10/I8), Wait Condition Fusion suite investigation (U9/I9), Road Topology KPIs via Query Compiler (U9/I9)",\n    "Archived duplicate Jia response task",\n    "Initiated re-estimation of Wait Condition Fusion workflow step estimates and async times"\n  ],\n  "memoriesExtracted": [\n    {"category": "fact", "key": "manager_out_of_country", "value": "User's manager is currently out of the country, reducing urgency of mandatory trainings"},\n    {"category": "fact", "key": "staging_suite_available", "value": "User now has a staging suite for Wait Condition Fusion investigation"},\n    {"category": "fact", "key": "jia_code_review", "value": "Jia sent a Slack message with code review feedback on the entity types data update CL (not the analyzer update one)"},\n    {"category": "preference", "key": "scheduling_approach", "value": "User prefers to let the scheduler slot tasks rather than manually picking what to do next"},\n    {"category": "fact", "key": "entity_types_cls", "value": "User has two entity types CLs: a data update one and an analyzer update one"},\n    {"category": "pattern", "key": "training_as_filler", "value": "User wants mandatory trainings kept at moderate priority to fill gaps while waiting on other tasks"}\n  ]\n}\n```	[]	[]	10	2026-04-21 20:57:34.936
