jctx-mo7ya1l1-cc1d34554	Mountain Chrysalis	I am going through huge life changes. I have ended the relationship with my ex-partner whom I dated for 12 years. I am 27. I have also worked a super stressful and highly demanding job for 3 and a half years now at NVIDIA, and I am slowly starting the transition out of it and into either music or neuroscience research. I do not structure my life in a typical left brained way, and I place far more value in investing in the future than in ticking away chores or todos. I am currently in what I call my 'Mountain Chrysalis', where I plan to work on myself and my passions intensely before emerging back into the world.	I am going through huge life changes. I have ended the relationship with my ex-partner whom I dated for 12 years. I am 27. I have also worked a super stressful and highly demanding job for 3 and a half years now at NVIDIA, and I am slowly starting the transition out of it and into either music or neuroscience research. I do not structure my life in a typical left brained way, and I place far more value in investing in the future than in ticking away chores or todos. I am currently in what I call my 'Mountain Chrysalis', where I plan to work on myself and my passions intensely before emerging back into the world.				t	session_1776709103518_hc4cf62	2026-04-21 01:33:44.964	2026-04-21 01:33:44.964
jctx-mo93ml7p-b9a51e052	Context Fusion L2PP Test Engineer	I work on a data and testing pipeline that is more or less: humans label data in some way, we ingest those labels, along with the sensor recordings from drive sessions in the geolocation of those labels (or vice versa, chicken/egg problem) and onboard those as 'tests' in our framework. That way, engineers can make changes to the neural networks or other in-car rules and see how it performs (without actuation of course, this is only testing that ONE drive path per-test, so we are only seeing differences in how the car thinks not how it behaves, during replay) with those changes before taking it to the road or merging it. The way they get that information is - when our tests run, they run in 'suites', and those report to a hive parquet data lake backend, where they can be read in redash through sql query dashboards. Each test has attached to it a collection of 'analyzers' which are python scripts that parse the simulation output log and do various checks and measurements to populate the parquet files during the suite run (job). Please note, I am trying a new methodology for work, where I do the minimum in order to eliminate stressors. So when advising me, we should focus on the things that are actively causing stress - i.e. people needing me to do things. Once the squeaky wheels are greased, I prefer to work on long term initiatives that will make my life easier in the long run at my job.	I work on a data and testing pipeline that is more or less: humans label data in some way, we ingest those labels, along with the sensor recordings from drive sessions in the geolocation of those labels (or vice versa, chicken/egg problem) and onboard those as 'tests' in our framework. That way, engineers can make changes to the neural networks or other in-car rules and see how it performs (without actuation of course, this is only testing that ONE drive path per-test, so we are only seeing differences in how the car thinks not how it behaves, during replay) with those changes before taking it to the road or merging it. The way they get that information is - when our tests run, they run in 'suites', and those report to a hive parquet data lake backend, where they can be read in redash through sql query dashboards. Each test has attached to it a collection of 'analyzers' which are python scripts that parse the simulation output log and do various checks and measurements to populate the parquet files during the suite run (job). Please note, I am trying a new methodology for work, where I do the minimum in order to eliminate stressors. So when advising me, we should focus on the things that are actively causing stress - i.e. people needing me to do things. Once the squeaky wheels are greased, I prefer to work on long term initiatives that will make my life easier in the long run at my job.				t	session_1776026596470_zisip0d	2026-04-21 20:51:14.53	2026-04-21 20:51:14.53
